{
  "texts": [
    "In § 7.1, we will generate continuum many full possibility frames with distinct Kripke-incomplete uni modal logics.",
    "Suppose φ and ψ are modal formulas such that the propositional variable p does not occur in ψ (or at least it only occurs in the form ⊤:= (p ∨ ¬p)).",
    "Then consider the following formula:♢ i (p ∧ ψ) → ♢ i (p ∧ φ) ∧ ♢ i (p ∧ ¬φ).",
    "(Split)We claim that any Kripke frame F that validates (Split) must also validate ¬♢ i ψ.",
    "Suppose ¬♢ i ψ is not valid over F, so there is a model M based on F and a world w such that M, w ⊨ ♢ i ψ."
  ]
}